Love this recipe. I've made it for many many brunch gatherings. That said, it does require a bit of finessing IMHO. My modifications: - Bail in the pecans. I did them once and didn't think that it was all that great. I may one day try crumbled bacon. - Cut the sugar down to 1/2 cup. 1 whole cup is way to much. - Syrup is nice (I've made it) but not necessary. Plain maple seems to work as well. - Take out of fridge at least an hour before putting in oven, or plan for much longer oven time. Very important - flip the bread over during the soaking/in the morning. That way its all soaked through on both sides.

