After reading many of the reviews and trying a test batch, I found a system for this recipe that worked very well for me. I used a very crusty, good & stale French country baguette (needed closer to 1 1/2 baguettes because these are very skinny), chilled the bread in the milk for about 18 hours until almost all milk was absorbed, and baked at 400 for a good 35 minutes, until the center was noticeably puffed up and some blueberry juice was bubbling. The texture of the bread was soft but not at all milky, and the blueberries and pecans added texture and crunch. The syrup rounded it out nicely. I'll definitely make this again.

