I have made this several times because it's easy and delicious, and because it can all be assembled the night before. For those who have had a problem with it being soupy, there are 3 remedies. First, reduce the milk to 2 1/4-2 1/2 cups. Second, use more bread. (Unfortun- ately, the recipe doesn't give the weight of the bread.) Third, after baking, let sit a few minutes before serving. This recipe does not need the blueberry syrup, or any for that matter.

