I think this recipe is tops! Do try it - if you don't want it so sweet you could use a tart berry like fresh cranberries. I've made this a few times and I've had mixed reviews- although I've never had anyone dislike it. Some people are still talking about it and others were a bit underwhelmed. I think that if you are a bread-pudding lover you will make this dish over and over again. I have had different results and I believe the inconsistencies that people have mentioned have to do with the thickness of the bread slices. The first time I made it, I cut the bread thicker than the recipe called for and it turned out great. The second time, I followed the recipe exactly and it was pretty moist. It makes a more custardy version with thin slices. Either way it is very good - if you have leftovers you can serve it with ice cream as another reviewer suggested.

