Absolutely FABULOUS!!!! This is to die for. Be warned - it's really a bread pudding and it's decadent enough to be dessert (but life is short, right?). You'll need to know your oven - I did have to pop it back into the oven for an extra 10 minutes. DO NOT skip the pecan step - the roasting and salt is a delicious and necessary contrast to the sweet. I didn't have whole milk on hand so I used a combination of half & half and skim milk. I prefer the sauce strained as per the recipe - and people familiar with real maple syrup wouldn't dare screw up the sauce with cornstarch.

