Rating: 3
I am surprised that this turned out with all the changes I made. I added 1 cup less of liquid to the milk mixture( I used half and half instead) and I did not soak overnight. I used a really soft french bread. I just let this sit about 15 minutes with the egg mixture on. The only thing I noticed was that the bread was very soft even after baking an additional 10 minutes. It was still good though. I only put one cup of blueberries on the toast; that was all I had. The blueberry syrup was wonderful. It was thin if you like thicker add a little cornstarch/water to it. I also only had a few pecans, I wish I would have had more.(This was a last minute throw together, can't you tell). The only reason I gave 3 forks instead of 4 was because of the bread being a bit too soft. Maybe actually soaking over night would better this. But this recipe is still delicious even w/o the soaking. Try it in a pinch.

