Rating: 4
I am a serious home cook and I entertain about 30 weekends a year. I have been culling recipes from Gourmet for at least 20 years. -- This might just be my favorite recipe of all. Why? It is incredibly easy and very forgiving. It can be halved or quadrupled. You can substitute any ingredients you choose. Heck, you don't even need to measure, really. I made this yesterday (hot day in June) by popping the baking dish into my toaster oven for 25 minutes at 375 degrees. The result was a great as ever. I make it so often that I have learned to always keep a bag of blueberries and a small container of pecans in the freezer, just in case. Have you got a finicky kid? A man that won't commit? A particularly hard to impress in-law? Just make this for breakfast and they will be singing your praises in no time.

